#define x and y
x = df.drop("class", axis=1)
y = df.pop("class")
In [ ]:
#split into train/test
xtrain, xtest, ytrain, ytest = train_test_split(x, y, test_size = 0.3, random_state=1)
In [ ]:
#creating + fitting model (and pre-pruning)

#after a lot of tweaking the hyperparams, i found a set that makes a pretty good outcome
dt = DecisionTreeClassifier(
    criterion="gini", 
    splitter="best",
    max_depth = 4,
    min_samples_leaf = 100,
    min_samples_split = 1000,
    random_state=1)
dt.fit(xtrain, ytrain)
